blurb_text: The 2007 federal election was held on 24 November 2007. In New South Wales, the elected candidates were Mark Arbib (Labor), Helen Coonan (Liberal), Doug Cameron (Labor), John Williams (Nationals), Marise Payne (Liberal), and Ursula Stephens (Labor).
